A cloud-based VPN admin portal built on AWS, enabling secure user provisioning, automated configuration, and centralized administration using WireGuard.

--Project Overview

![Solution Diagram](vpnAdminPortal.png)

Creating a admin portal for current VPN server for below purposes 

     - Create and terminate VPN users
     - Automatically generate WireGuard configuration files
     - Store user profiles and .conf file securely in AWS S3
     - Push VPN configuration updates to EC2 via AWS Systems Manager (SSM)
     - Send VPN access files to users via AWS SES
     - Manage access through a secure web-based admin portal


Workflow – Create VPN User
    1. Admin logs in via Amazon Cognito
    2. Admin submits user creation request via Admin Portal
    3. API Gateway triggers Lambda function
    4. Lambda:
        4.1 Generates WireGuard key pair
        4.2 Creates .conf file
        4.3 Stores user data in S3
        4.4 Sends command via SSM to update WireGuard server
        4.5 Sends configuration file to user via SES
    5. User receives .conf file and connects to VPN

Workflow – Terminate VPN User
    1. Admin selects user from portal
    2. API Gateway triggers Lambda
    3. Lambda:
        3.1 Removes user from WireGuard config via SSM
        3.2 Deletes user record from S3
    4. VPN access is immediately revoked


Tech Stack
   - Frontend
        HTML / CSS / JavaScript
        Hosted on Amazon S3
        Delivered via CloudFront
  - Backend
        AWS Lambda (Python)  
        API Gateway (REST API)
  - Authentication
        Amazon Cognito (OAuth2 / OpenID Connect)
  - Infrastructure
        EC2 (Ubuntu + WireGuard VPN)
        AWS Systems Manager (SSM)
  - Storage
        Amazon S3 (User data & config files)
  - Email
        Amazon SES (Send VPN config to users)


